-- For a storage, it's possible to define one or two storage dimension(s).
-- This dimension will be used to propose position value when user try to store a
-- children storage or an aliquot into the storage or to build storage layout.
--
-- 4 dimension defintions are supported by the system:
--     1- type = 'list' + size = NULL: 
--			=> allow user to record predefined values that will be selected during
--             children storage/aliquot position defintion (see form alias 
--             std_storage_coordinates).
--
--     2- type = 'alphabetical' + size : [integer value]
--			=> allow system to build  predefined list of alphabetical values
--             (A, B, C, D, etc). The number of letter depends of the size value (< 24).
--              
--     3- type = 'integer' + size : [integer value]
--			=> allow system to build predefined list of integer values
